<% else %>

<div class="help_accordion">
	<h3>Choose Clients</h3>
		<div class="help_accordion">
			<h3>What do you do here?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>This is where you will choose the clients you want to work with and try and make a sale
						with.</p>
				</div>
			<h3>What is the total clients available number?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>This is the total number of clients you are able to have at any given time.</p>
					<p>Once you reach zero, you will not be able to select anymore clients until you
						either make a sell or release a client.</p>
					<p>To release a client, go to the My Clients Help menu option.</p>
				</div>
			<h3>What is the high, medium, and low priorities allowed number?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>This number represents the restriction you have for each type of client, and 
						each client is considered a type of priority (high, medium, and low).  The
						number will go down when:</p>
					<p>1) You choose a client that has the same priority associated with that allowed number.<br />
					   2) The total clients available number is less than the allowed number.</p>
					<p>When you reach zero, you will not be able to select a client with that priority until
						you either make a sell or release a client with that same priority.</p>
					<p>To release a client, go to the My Clients Help menu option.</p>
				</div>
			<h3>What does high, medium, and low priority clients actually mean?</h3>
				<div>
					<p><h4>High Priority</h4>- The client was sold an ad last year (easier to sell again 
						this year).</p>
					<p><h4>Medium Priority</h4>- The client was sold an ad two or three years ago (maybe 
						or maybe not sell this year).</p>
					<p><h4>Low Priority</h4>- The client was either never sold an ad before or was sold
						an add more than three years ago (ideally the hardest to sell to).</p>
				</div>
			<h3>What happens when you click the Add button?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>This will make this client a part of you My Clients, so you can record actions and of course
						sell an ad to them! :)</p>
					<p>When you click on the Add button, the button will go away and a message will tell you that you
						were given the client.  If you reach the maximum number of total clients available, then you
						will not be able to select any more clients until you either make a sell or release a client.</p>
					<p>Also, once you have a client, no one else will be able to grab it.  The only way 
						another student might is if you released the client.</p>
					<p>To release a client, go to the My Clients Help menu option.</p>
				</div>
		</div>
	<h3>My Clients</h3>
		<div class="help_accordion">
			<h3>What do you do here?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>This is where you will see your active, completed (sold), and released clients.</p>
				</div>
			<h3>What can you do with active clients?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>You will be able to record actions (first contact, presentation, and sale) to a client.
						To do this, simply click anywhere within the sticky note and it will take you to the 
						Client's Activity Page.</p>
				</div>
			<h3>What can you do with completed clients?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>This will take you to the Client's Activity Page where you will be able to delete an activity 
						or comment associated with this client.</p>
					<p>Keep in mind:<br />
						1) You can only delete an activity in reverse order by deleting the sale first, then presentation,
						and then first contact (you may delete a comment at any time).<br />
						2) Once you delete the sale, the client will now be considered an active client again.<br />
						3) Deleting an activity that has points associated with it will also delete from your total
						points.
					</p>
				</div>
			<h3>What can you do with released clients?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>This is more of a reference of what activity you did with the client, and you will not be
						able to delete or create activities with it (except for a comment).</p>
				</div>
			<h3>How do you release a client?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>If you do not want the client anymore, and you want to choose another one, you can use
						this option of releasing a client.</p>
					<p>To do this: <br /> 
						1) Hover the mouse over the sticky note of the client you want to release (you will only
						be able to delete an active client, not a completed client).<br />
						2) Click on the small x that appears in the top left corner.<br />
						3) A pop up box will appear making sure if you want to release it, along with a comment
						box if you want to leave a comment (optional).<br />
						4) Click release and that's it!</p>
				</div>
			<h3>What happens when you release a client?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>The client will go to your released client section, and you will now be able to select 
						another client from the Choose Clients tab.</p>
					<p>Also, if you had any points associated with this client, you will still keep them. :)</p>
				</div>
			<h3>Why are the sticky notes green, yellow, white, or gray?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>The colors are associated to each type of priority (execept gray):<br />
						<h4>Green</h4>- The client is a high priority client.<br />
						<h4>Yellow</h4>- The client is a medium priority client.<br />
						<h4>White</h4>- The client is a low priority client.<br />
						<h4>Gray</h4>- The client is a released client.
					</p>
				</div>
		</div>
	
	<h3>Client Activity Page</h3>
		<div class="help_accordion">
			<h3>What do you do here?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>This is where you will record activities with a client (record a first contact, presentation,
						or sale).</p>
				</div>
			<h3>How do you get here?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>Go to your My Clients and click on the client's sticky note that you want.</p>
				</div>
			<h3>How do you edit the client's information?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>Click on the Edit this client link to take you to a form.  Here you will be able to update
						or edit the client's information (subject to teacher's approval of course).</p>
				</div>
			<h3>How do you record an activity?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>You will need to go in natural order of progression (first contact, then presentation, and
						finally a sale).</p>
					<p>!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!</p>
				</div>
		</div>
	
	<h3>Submit Client</h3>
		<div class="help_accordion">
			<h3>What do you do here?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>You will be able to view unapproved and pending clients, as well as submit a new client to
						be used in the project.</p>
				</div>
			<h3>How does submitting a new client work?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>First and foremost, check the pending and unapproved client lists below to make sure that
						the client you want to submit has not already been submitted before.</p>
					<p>Then simply fill out the form of a business you would like to try and sell an ad to.</p>
					<p>The client will then be put in the pending clients list where a teacher will either approve
						or unapprove your submission (Student Life will actually make the approval process, it's 
						just that the teacher will approve it in Ad It).</p>
					<p>If the client is approved, the client will be added your active clients and you will be 
						able to work with that client.  If unapproved, then you will not be able to work with 
						that client.</p>
				</div>
			<h3>Why can I not submit a new client?</h3>
				<div>
					<p>If you already have the maximum number of total clients available, then you will not be 
						able to submit a new client.</p>
					<p>The reason being that if your submitted client was approved, it will be assigned to you,
						and you will then have one more clients than you are supposed to have.</p>
				</div>
		</div>
	<h3>Navigation</h3>
		<div>
			<p>Here is our recommendation for navigating through Ad It:</p>
			<p>1) First and foremost, we do not recommend using the Back and Forward buttons on the web browser.<br />
				2) The navigation bar (Choose Clients, My Clients, Submit Client, and Help) is your oprtions for 
				the main pages in Ad It.<br />
				3) Now of course, there are other pages within each of the main pages that you will view or go
				to, and for those we recommend using the links that start with "Back" to go to the previous page.</p>
		</div>
</div>

<% end %>


